{
  "text": "Internal fixation (IF) for femoral neck fracture has many advantages such as minimal blood loss, short operating time, and low infection rate [CITATION_1] . The trend is, however, to treat displaced fractures with hemiarthroplasty due to a high reoperation rate of IF in comparison to arthroplasty (40% vs. 11%), and also due to better functional outcome [CITATION_2] . The high reoperation rate is mainly due to early failure of fixation.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "23657080",
    "[CITATION_2]": "24600338"
  },
